projecttitle: Watershed Capacity Building for Climate Change Adaptation
project_descrip: Short: WATERSHED CAPACITY BUILDING FOR CLIMATE CHANGE ADAPTATION Long: The project aims to improve access to and enhance the reliability of water supply for domestic purposes and irrigation for communities living in the watersheds of Nepal river systems which are significantly vulnerable to climate change
shortdescription: WATERSHED CAPACITY BUILDING FOR CLIMATE CHANGE ADAPTATION
longdescription: The project aims to improve access to and enhance the reliability of water supply for domestic purposes and irrigation for communities living in the watersheds of Nepal river systems which are significantly vulnerable to climate change

project_descrip: Short: WATER AND SANITATION Long: The project comprises of 2 components: 1: Extension of the methane gas generation capacity at the Cambérène wastewater treatment plant in Dakar and, 2: Supply of treated wastewater for irrigation for urban horticulture areas in Pikine/Niayes and Patte d'Oie in Dakar.
purposename: Water supply and sanitation - large systems
longdescription: The project comprises of 2 components: 1: Extension of the methane gas generation capacity at the Cambérène wastewater treatment plant in Dakar and, 2: Supply of treated wastewater for irrigation for urban horticulture areas in Pikine/Niayes and Patte d'Oie in Dakar.

projecttitle: Farm Income Enhancement and Forest Conservation project 2 (FIEFOC 2)
project_descrip: Short: FARM INCOME ENHANCEMENT AND FOREST CONSERVATION PROJECT 2 (FIEFOC 2) Long: The project's specific objectives are to improve household incomes, food security and climate resilience through development of agricultural infrastructure, specifically, 5 new small and medium scale irrigation schemes and related civil works, packaged with agribusiness development and integrated sustainable natural resources management.
shortdescription: FARM INCOME ENHANCEMENT AND FOREST CONSERVATION PROJECT 2 (FIEFOC 2)
longdescription: The project's specific objectives are to improve household incomes, food security and climate resilience through development of agricultural infrastructure, specifically, 5 new small and medium scale irrigation schemes and related civil works, packaged with agribusiness development and integrated sustainable natural resources management.
